    public class StrandList
extends java.util.AbstractList<Strand>
    A list of Strand that coordinates strand divisions etc to ensure the segmentation of nucleotides is consistent.

      • divideStrand

        public void divideStrand(int strandIndex,
                         int nucIndexInStrand)
        Divides one strand into two separate strands. The division occurs immediately before nucIndexInStrand, so after the division, the Nuc at nucIndexInStrand-1 will be the last Nuc in Strand, while the Nuc previously at nucIndexInStrand will be the first Nuc in the newly created subsequent strand.

      • divideStrand

        public void divideStrand(Strand strand,
                         int nucIndexInStrand)
        Divides one strand into two separate strands. The division occurs immediately before nucIndexInStrand, so after the division, the Nuc at nucIndexInStrand-1 will be the last Nuc in Strand, while the Nuc previously at nucIndexInStrand will be the first Nuc in the newly created subsequent strand.
